# Rule: Privilege Escalation Attempt
# Detects non-admin users attempting to access admin endpoints
# MITRE ATT&CK: T1068 — Exploitation for Privilege Escalation

name: "CRITICAL — Privilege Escalation Attempt"

# 'any' type — alert on EVERY single match
# Privilege escalation is serious enough to alert every time
type: any

index: ir-security-events-*

filter:
  - term:
      event_type: "privilege_escalation"

alert:
  - debug

alert_text: |
  PRIVILEGE ESCALATION ATTEMPT

  MITRE ATT&CK: T1068 — Exploitation for Privilege Escalation
  Severity: CRITICAL

  A non-admin user attempted to access an admin-only endpoint.
  This could indicate an attacker testing for authorization flaws.

  Action Required:
  - Investigate the user account immediately
  - Check if the account has been compromised
  - Review recent activity from this user
  - Consider temporarily disabling the account